    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team concludes that the CFD hemolysis model meets the required credibility levels for all 13 ASME V&V 40 factors at Model Risk Level 2. Seven factors were formally assessed and all achieved their required gradation levels. The remaining six factors were determined not applicable or scoped out consistent with MRL 2 guidance. The model is accepted for use in identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device, with the relative hemolysis index acceptance criterion (RH < 1) confirmed as the decision metric.",
